# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 17: chemical short-range order in a high-entropy alloy
#
# Build an equimolar fcc CoCrFeNi solid solution with the chemical species
# assigned at random, then drive it toward chemical equilibrium with a hybrid
# molecular dynamics / Monte Carlo scheme: molecular dynamics moves the atoms
# while fix atom/swap proposes exchanges of the chemical identities of pairs
# of atoms, accepted with the Metropolis criterion.  The alloy develops
# chemical short-range order, which is quantified by the Warren-Cowley
# parameters (see plot.py).  Uses the EAM potential of Farkas and Caro,
# J. Mater. Res. 33, 3218 (2018), designed for fcc high-entropy alloys.

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

variable T equal 700.0

# 1) build a random equimolar CoCrFeNi crystal (fcc, 8x8x8 = 2048 atoms)
lattice fcc 3.56
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 3.56 3.56 3.56
region box block 0 8 0 8 0 8
create_box 4 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (28.48 28.48 28.48)
  1 by 1 by 1 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 2048 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (28.48 28.48 28.48)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.000 seconds
# randomly assign exactly one quarter of the sites to each element
set group all type/subset 2 512 12345
Setting atom values ...
  512 settings made for type/subset
set type 1   type/subset 3 512 23456
Setting atom values ...
  512 settings made for type/subset
set type 1   type/subset 4 512 34567
Setting atom values ...
  512 settings made for type/subset
mass 1 58.933   # Co
mass 2 51.996   # Cr
mass 3 55.845   # Fe
mass 4 58.693   # Ni
pair_style eam/alloy
pair_coeff * * FeNiCrCoCu-heafixed.setfl Co Cr Fe Ni

variable peat equal pe/count(all)

# 2) thermalize the atomic positions at temperature T (no swaps yet)
velocity all create ${T} 9988 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
velocity all create 700 9988 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix md all npt temp ${T} ${T} 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix md all npt temp 700 ${T} 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
fix md all npt temp 700 700 0.1 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 500
thermo_style custom step temp pe press
run 2000
Neighbor list info ...
  update: every = 1 steps, delay = 0 steps, check = yes
  max neighbors/atom: 2000, page size: 100000
  master list distance cutoff = 7.80375
  ghost atom cutoff = 7.80375
  binsize = 3.901875, bins = 8 8 8
  1 neighbor lists, perpetual/occasional/extra = 1 0 0
  (1) pair eam/alloy, perpetual
      attributes: half, newton on
      pair build: half/bin/atomonly/newton
      stencil: half/bin/3d
      bin: standard
